    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Err<T,E>
    Represents the error of a wrong execution of an operation; Example: in a file reading, a Result could be Result<String, IOException>, where failing would return Err <IOException>.
    Main
    Ignored
    None<T>
    Represents an empty value, as it was a 'null' value;
    Ok<T,E>
    Represents the result of the correct execution of an operation; Example: in a file reading, a Result could be Result<String, IOException>, where the correct execution would return Ok<String>.
    Option<T>
    Represents an optional value using two states: Some if containing a non-null value, or None if there is no value, this offers a series of advantages over Java's null pointers:
    Result<T,E>
    A type used for returning and propagating errors.
    Some<T>
    Represents an existing and non-null value.
    ThrowingRunnable<E>
    A Runnable that allows to throw one single kind of Throwable.
    ThrowingSupplier<T,E>
    A Supplier that allows to throw one single kind of Exception.
    Tuple0
    A tuple containing no values, this is also known as 'empty'.
    Tuple1<T>
    A tuple containing 1 non-null value.
    Tuple1Record<T>
    A tuple containing 1 non-null value.
    Tuple2<T,U>
    A tuple containing 2 non-null values, all of them with possibly different types.
    Tuple2Record<T,U>
    A tuple containing 2 non-null values, all of them with possibly different types.
    Tuple3<T,U,V>
    A tuple containing 3 non-null values, all of them with possibly different types.
    Tuple3Record<T,U,V>
    A tuple containing 3 non-null values, all of them with possibly different types.
    Tuple4<T,U,V,W>
    A tuple containing 4 non-null values, all of them with possibly different types.
    Tuple4Record<T,U,V,W>
    A tuple containing 4 non-null values, all of them with possibly different types.

    A tuple containing 5 non-null values, all of them with possibly different types.

    Tuple6<T,U,V,W,X,Y>

    Tuple7<T,U,V,W,X,Y,Z>
    A tuple containing 7 non-null values, all of them with possibly different types.
    Tuple7Record<T,U,V,W,X,Y,Z>
    A tuple containing 7 non-null values, all of them with possibly different types.
    Tuples
    Tuples are collection of values, where each element of the tuple can have a different type, and they might hold from 0 to 7 values, for example, a tuple that holds 3 values is a Tuple3.
